1. Install XAMPP in Windows and LAMPP in Ubuntu
2. Boot into Linux and record your Windows htdocs folder 
_________________________________________________________________________________________
(say /home/user/OS/xampp/htdocs)
_________________________________________________________________________________________

3. Go to /opt/lampp/etc and edit httpd.conf and make the following changes (you will need root permissions to do so)
  >>1)
    Replace
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    #DocumentRoot "/opt/lamp/htdocs"
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    by
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    #DocumentRoot "YOUR_DOCUMENT_LOCATION"
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    
      EXAMPLE : 
      _________________________________________________________________________________________
      #DocumentRoot "/home/user/WEB"
      _________________________________________________________________________________________
      
  >>2)
    Replace
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    Directory "/opt/lampp/htdocs" 
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    by
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    Directory "YOUR_DOCUMENT_LOCATION"
    _________________________________________________________________________________________

      EXAMPLE : 
      _________________________________________________________________________________________
      Directory "/home/user/WEB"
      _________________________________________________________________________________________
      
  >>3) In the "IfModule unixd_module" (use ctrl + f)
    Replace
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    User daemon
    Group daemon
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    by
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    User Directory_Username
    Group Directory_Groupname
    _________________________________________________________________________________________
    
    EXAMPLE : 
      _________________________________________________________________________________________
      User User
      Group User
      _________________________________________________________________________________________
You can find Directory_Username and Directory_Groupname using terminal comand "ls -l". 
In here my "WEB" directory adress is "/home/user/WEB", so this was what i do to get Directory_Username and Directory_Groupname :

EXAMPLE:
_________________________________________________________________________________________
ls -l /home/user
_________________________________________________________________________________________
